THE GAME OF PAPER, ROCK, SCISSORS:

We have used enumeration types and typedefs to create this game.
If you want to understand the code, you should play the game
first.  Here are the instructions, which you can also get
by typing i when playing the game:

---
PAPER, ROCK, SCISSORS:
   In this game p is for "paper," r is for "rock," and s
   is for "scissors."  Both the player and the machine will
   choose one of p, r, or s.  If the two choices are the same,
   then the game is a tie.  Otherwise:
      "paper covers the rock"     (a win for paper),
      "rock breaks the scissors"  (a win for rock),
      "scissors cut the paper"    (a win for scissors).

   There are other allowable inputs:
      g   for game status   (the number of wins so far),
      h   for help,
      i   for instructions  (reprint these instructions),
      q   for quit          (to quit the game).

   This game is played repeatedly until q is entered.

   Good luck!
